text: Dealing with sensory overload Hey guys  I realized that between anxiety and ADHD  And possible other things  I m not sure  this might be a fairly common thing  I thought I d share  Basically  sensory overload is when you get too overwhelmed that everything becomes a little too much  People chewing is too loud  people talking is annoying  every little sound is overwhelming  maybe other senses are getting worked up too  mine is usually auditory  so I thought I would share some of my coping mechanisms to help you guys out    Tell the people around you that you re dealing with sensory overload right now  so you might be a little snappier than usual  This seriously helps  because a lot of times people assume you re being rude  Find a quiet space to distance yourself from other people  This helps your senses to reset and helps everything just calm down  Do something easy and absorbing to help distract you  Do some meditation or some colouring  Something that doesn t require too much concentration  I ve found that tasks with repetitive motions are very soothing  Calming music like wind chimes can help as well These are all the things I could think of  let me know if you all have other things that help you  Cheers
summary: Sensory overload is a common condition that can be linked to anxiety and ADHD. It can be caused by people talking too much, chewing too loud, people talking in a loud voice, or repetitive repetitive motions, or wind chimes.
